# Learning How To Learn: Memory and studying tips

* Create strong visual cues (our brains are better at remembering visual and spatial things)
* Create flashcards and review them before bed to stimulate deeper retention during sleep.
* Interleave your subject matter.
* Repeat the testing process, with greater intervals between each repetition as the material becomes more engrained.
* Use the "memory palace" technique, placing very memorable items in your palace to prompt you to remember various things.

